Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.64,0:00:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&\pos(3500,-300)}So in college.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.44,0:00:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a government major which means\NI had to write a lot of papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.48,0:00:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when a normal student writes a paper
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.15,0:00:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they might spread the work\Nout a little like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.80,0:00:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.84,0:00:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You get started maybe a little slowly\Nbut you get enough done in the first week
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.12,0:00:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that some have your days later on\Neverything gets done things stay civil
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would want to do that like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.20,0:00:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.44,0:00:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I would I would have it all ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.12,0:00:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But then than that the people would come\Nalong and then I would kind of do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.84,0:00:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would happen every single paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.68,0:00:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But then came my 90 page senior thesis\Npaper you're supposed to spend a year on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.96,0:01:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew for a paper like that my normal\Nworkflow was not an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.56,0:01:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was way too big a project.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.96,0:01:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I planned things out and I decided\NI kind of had to go something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.76,0:01:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how the year would go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.08,0:01:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it started off light.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.36,0:01:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I bumped it up in the middle months.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.68,0:01:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at the end I would kick it up\Ninto high gears a little staircase.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.88,0:01:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How hard could it be\Njust walk up the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.36,0:01:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No big deal right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.04,0:01:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But then funniest thing happened those\Nfirst few months they came and went.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.68,0:01:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I I couldn't quite do stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.64,0:01:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had an awesome new revised plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.76,0:01:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.40,0:01:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But then those middle months\Nactually went by.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.64,0:01:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't really write words.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then two months turned into one month
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.20,0:01:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,turned into two weeks\Nand one day I woke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.84,0:01:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,With three days until the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.44,0:01:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Still not having written a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.56,0:01:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I did the only thing I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.60,0:02:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote 90 pages over 72 hours\Npulling not one but two all nighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.48,0:02:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans are not supposed\Nto put two all nighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sprinted across campus dove in slow\Nmotion and got it in of the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.96,0:02:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I thought that was\Nthe end of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.68,0:02:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But a week later I get a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.72,0:02:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say is this Tim Urban.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.52,0:02:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.96,0:02:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say we need\Nto talk about your thesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.16,0:02:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.52,0:02:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say it's the best\None we've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.08,0:02:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That did not happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.36,0:02:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a very very bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I just.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanted to enjoy that one moment when\Nall of you thought this guy's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.84,0:02:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No no.\NIt was very very bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.48,0:02:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway today I'm a writer blogger guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.88,0:03:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I write the blog Wait But Why.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.56,0:03:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And a couple of years ago I decided\Nto write about Krastev nation my behaviors
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.84,0:03:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,are always perplexed the non\Nprocrastinators around me and I wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.28,0:03:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to explain to the non\Nprocrastinators of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.44,0:03:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What goes on in the heads
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of procrastinators and why\Nwe are the where we are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.56,0:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a hypothesis that the brains
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.20,0:03:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of procrastinators were actually different\Nthan the brains of other people
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and to testis I found an MRI lab\Nthat she'd let me scan both my brain
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.48,0:03:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the brain of a proven non\Nprocrastinator and I so I could compare
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.16,0:03:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,them and I actually brought\Nthem here to show you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.64,0:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want you to take a look carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to see if you can notice the difference\Nand I know that if you're not a trained
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.73,0:03:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,brain expert it's not that obvious\Nbut just take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.68,0:03:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,OK so here's the brain\Nof a non procrastinator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.40,0:03:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's my brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.80,0:03:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:04:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Both brains have a rational decision maker
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.32,0:04:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in them but the procrastinators brain\Nalso has an Instant Gratification Monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.12,0:04:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what does this mean\Nfor the procrastinator.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.84,0:04:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well it means everything's\Nfine until this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rational decision maker will make\Nthe rational decision to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.75,0:04:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,productive with the monkey\Ndoesn't like that plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.40,0:04:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So he actually takes the wheel and he says\Nactually let's read the entire Wikipedia
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,page of the Nancy Kerrigan\NTonya Harding scandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I just remember that that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.68,0:04:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.60,0:04:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we're going to go over to the fridge
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to see if it's anything\Nnew in there since ten
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.00,0:04:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,After that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.68,0:04:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go on a YouTube spiral\Nthat starts with videos of Richard Fineman
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.60,0:04:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about magnets\Nand ends much much later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.24,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With us watching interviews\Nwith Justin Bieber's mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.44,0:04:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh that's going to take a while so we're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.74,0:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,not going to really have room\Non the schedule for any work today sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.44,0:05:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what is going on here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.60,0:05:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the Instant Gratification Monkey does not\Nseem like a guy you want behind the wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.40,0:05:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives entirely in the present moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.44,0:05:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He has no memory of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.48,0:05:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No knowledge of the future and only\Ncares about two things easy and fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.44,0:05:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in the animal world\Nthat works fine if you're a dog and you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,spend your whole life doing nothing\Nother than easy and fun things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.88,0:05:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You were a huge success.\NAnd.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.52,0:05:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To the monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.00,0:05:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans are just another animal species
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.24,0:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep well slept well fed\Nand propagating into the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.72,0:05:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Which in tribal times\Nmight have worked OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.96,0:05:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you haven't noticed now we're not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in tribal times we're\Nin an advanced civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.78,0:05:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the monkey does not know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.08,0:05:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is why we have another guy in our\Nbrain the rational decision maker
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.76,0:05:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,who gives us the ability to do\Nthings no other animal can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.88,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We can visualize the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.88,0:05:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see the big picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.48,0:06:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can make long term plans and he\Nwants to take all of that into account
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.20,0:06:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wants to just have us do whatever\Nmakes sense to be doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now sometimes it makes sense to be doing\Nthings that are easy and fun like when
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.76,0:06:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you're having dinner or going to bed\Nor enjoying well earned leisure time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why there's an overlap.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.64,0:06:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But other times it makes much more sense
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.52,0:06:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to be doing things that are harder\Nand less pleasant for the sake of the big
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.16,0:06:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,picture and that's when\Nwe have a conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.16,0:06:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the procrastinator that conflict\Ntends to end the certain way every time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving him spending a lot of time\Nin this orange zone and easy and fun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.28,0:06:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,place that's entirely out\Nof the Make Sense circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I call it the dark playground.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.04,0:06:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.88,0:06:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The dark playground is a place that all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.12,0:06:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of you procrastinators\Nout there know very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where leisure activities happen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.84,0:06:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,at times when leisure activities\Nare not supposed to be happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.52,0:06:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The fun you have in the dark playground
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.96,0:07:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't actually fun because it's completely\Nunearned and the air is filled with guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.88,0:07:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,dread anxiety self-hatred all those\Ngood procrastinator feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question is in this situation\Nwith the monkey behind the wheel how does
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the procrastinator ever get himself over\Nhere to this Blue Zone a less pleasant
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.75,0:07:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,place but were really\Nimportant things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.\NIt turns out that the procrastinator has
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.32,0:07:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a guardian angel someone who's always\Nlooking down on him and watching over him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.52,0:07:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in his darkest moments someone\Ncalled the panic monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.52,0:07:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.80,0:07:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The panic monster is dormant most\Nof the time but he suddenly wakes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Anytime a deadline gets too close or\Nthere's danger of public embarrassment
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.32,0:07:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a career disaster or some\Nother scary consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.00,0:07:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And importantly he's the only thing\Nthat the monkey is terrified of.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.00,0:07:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He became very relevant in my life pretty\Nrecently because people have Ted reached
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.76,0:08:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out to me about six months ago\Nand invited me to do a TED talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.20,0:08:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now of course I said yes it's always been
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a dream of mine to have done\Na TED talk in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.24,0:08:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the middle of all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.04,0:08:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,excitement the rational decision makers\Nseem to have something else on his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.10,0:08:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He was saying.\NWe're not clear on what we just accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.00,0:08:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,do we get what's going to be now happening\None day in the future we need to sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and work on this right\Nnow and the monkey said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally agree but also let's just open\NGoogle Earth and let's zoom
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.48,0:08:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in to the bottom of India like\N200 feet above the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.72,0:08:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to scroll up to two and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.28,0:08:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hours to get to the top of the country\Nso we can get a better feel for India.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:08:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what we did that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.64,0:09:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As six months turned into four and then\Ntwo and then one the people of Ted decided
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.96,0:09:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to release the speakers\Nand I opened up the website.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.30,0:09:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was my face\Nstaring right back at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And guess who woke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the panic Monster starts losing his
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.48,0:09:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,mind and a few seconds later\Nthe whole systems and mayhem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.64,0:09:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the monkey you remember he's terrified
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.32,0:09:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the panic mounts or\Nboom he's up the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.72,0:09:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally finally the rational decision
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.60,0:09:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,maker can take the wheel and I\Ncan start working on the talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the panic monster explains all kinds\Nof pretty insane procrastinated behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.44,0:09:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,like how someone like me could spend two\Nweeks unable to start the opening sentence
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.36,0:09:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of a paper and then miraculously\Nfind the unbelievable worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.92,0:09:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Work ethic stay up all\Nnight and write eight pages
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.48,0:09:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and this entire situation\Nwith the three characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.76,0:10:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the procrastinators system.\NIt's not pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.08,0:10:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the end it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.64,0:10:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is what I decided\Nto write about on the blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a couple of years ago now when I did\NI was amazed by the response literally
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.00,0:10:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of e-mails came in from all\Ndifferent kinds of people from all over
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the world doing all\Ndifferent kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people who were nurses
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and bankers and painters and engineers\Nand lots and lots of Ph.D. students.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.84,0:10:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were all writing\Nsaying the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.72,0:10:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have this problem too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But what struck me was the contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.60,0:10:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,between the light tone of the post\Nand the heaviness of these e-mails.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.04,0:10:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,These people were writing with intense
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.79,0:10:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,frustration about what procrastination\Nhad done to their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.04,0:10:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,about what this monkey had done to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought about this and I said\Nwell the procrastinator system works.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.92,0:10:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are all these people\Nin such a dark place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.84,0:10:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well it turns out that there's\Ntwo kinds of procrastination.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.08,0:11:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I've talked about today
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.08,0:11:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the examples I've given they all have\Ndeadlines and there's deadlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.20,0:11:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The effects of procrastination are
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.80,0:11:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,contained to the short term because\Nthe panic monster gets involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's a second kind
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.68,0:11:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of procrastination that happens\Nin situations when there is no deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.72,0:11:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to have a career you want
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.36,0:11:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a self starter something\Nin the arts something entrepreneurial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.96,0:11:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no deadlines on those things\Nfirst because nothing's happening first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.44,0:11:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Not until you've gone out and done
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.76,0:11:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the hard work to get some\Nmomentum to get things going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.48,0:11:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also all kinds of important things\Noutside of your career that don't involve
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.94,0:11:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,any deadlines like seeing your family or\Nexercising and taking care of your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.24,0:11:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Working on your relationship or getting\Nout of a relationship that isn't working.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.64,0:11:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if procrastinators only mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of doing these hard things is the panic\NMonastir that's a problem because in all
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.16,0:11:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of these non deadlines situations\Nthe panic monster doesn't show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.04,0:11:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to wake up for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.36,0:11:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the effects of procrastination are not\Ncontain they just extend outward forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.04,0:11:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's this long term kind
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.44,0:12:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of procrastination\Nthat's much less visible and much less
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.32,0:12:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,talked about than the fun of your\Nshort term deadline based kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.84,0:12:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's usually suffer quietly and privately.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can be the source of a huge amount\Nof long term unhappiness and regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.64,0:12:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought that's why these people are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.12,0:12:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,emailing and that's why\Nthey're in such a bad place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.92,0:12:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that they're cramming for some\Nproject it's that long term
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.08,0:12:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,procrastination has made them feel like\Na spectator at times in their own lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.72,0:12:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the frustration was not that they\Ncouldn't achieve their dreams it's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.76,0:12:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that they weren't even able\Nto start chasing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.72,0:12:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.92,0:12:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I read these emails and I had\Na little bit of an epiphany
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.28,0:12:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that I don't think non\Nprocrastinators exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.12,0:12:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NI think all of you are procrastinators.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.04,0:12:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you might not all be\Na mess like some of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.88,0:12:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And some of you may have a healthy\Nrelationship with deadlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.12,0:13:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember the monkeys sneakiest trick
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is when the deadlines aren't there\Nnow to show you one last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.44,0:13:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I call this a life calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.44,0:13:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one box for every week\Nof a 90 year life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.48,0:13:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that many boxes especially since\Nwe've already used a bunch of those
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.68,0:13:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so I think we need to all take\Na long hard look at that calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.00,0:13:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And we need to think about what we're
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.60,0:13:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,really procrastinating on because everyone\Nis procrastinating on something in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.88,0:13:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to stay aware of the\Ninstant gratification monkey
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.52,0:13:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a job for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.80,0:13:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And because there's not that many boxes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on there it's a job that should\Nprobably start today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.60,0:13:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well maybe not today but.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.04,0:13:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.64,0:13:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometime soon.\NThank you.
